HTTP Header Injection using curl:
  

  Step1:
  		Browser send a request like this:
  			GET / http / 1.1
  				host: 		google.com
  				User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0
  				Accept: 	*/*

  		GET --> Http Method
  		Host,User-Agent,Accept --> All are headers(Extra info about the request)

  Step2:
  	We inject header do:
  		1.spoof identity(fake browser,fake referer)
  		2.Test Security(Host Referer Section,Referer Check Bypass)
  		3.Send Session Tokens(Via Cookie header)
  		4.Custom testing(X-Forward-For,Authorization,etc..)

  Step3:
  	curl Commands:
  		we use curl commads to send http request from terminal
  			ex1:curl http://httpbin.org/get




ğŸ“˜ Topic: HTTP Header Injection using curl

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ§  What is a Header?

- Header = Extra info in HTTP request
- Examples: User-Agent, Referer, Host, Cookie

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ’¥ Why Inject Headers?

- Spoof browser / user identity
- Test for vulnerabilities
- Bypass referer checks
- Simulate logged-in users (cookies)

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ›  curl Basics:

Command format:
curl -H "Header-Name: value" [URL]

Example:
curl -H "User-Agent: Hacker" http://example.com

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ” Common Header Injection Examples:

1ï¸âƒ£ Spoof User-Agent
curl -H "User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0" http://httpbin.org/headers

2ï¸âƒ£ Fake Referer
curl -H "Referer: https://evil.com" http://httpbin.org/headers

3ï¸âƒ£ Host Header Injection
curl -H "Host: attacker.com" http://httpbin.org/headers

4ï¸âƒ£ Custom Header
curl -H "X-Test: value" http://httpbin.org/headers

5ï¸âƒ£ Cookie Injection
curl -H "Cookie: sessionid=xyz123" http://httpbin.org/cookies

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ“Œ Multiple Headers in One Request:

curl -H "User-Agent: Mozilla" -H "Referer: evil.com" http://httpbin.org/headers

---------------------------------------------
âš  Why google.com fails?

- Google has firewall, doesn't reflect back headers
- Blocks curl-like requests
- Use httpbin.org or test sites for practice

---------------------------------------------
ğŸ§ª Safe Testing Site:

http://httpbin.org/headers

- Reflects back all headers sent
- Use for learning, testing injections

---------------------------------------------
